Description.
WORKER (n=6) (
Fig. 39A–C
): HL (0.94–1.04); HW (0.88–0.96); ML (0.60–0.68); SL (0.66–0.72); MOD (0.20–0.23); PNW (0.61–0.68); WL (1.20–1.36); PSL (0.30–0.34); PL (0.62–0.73); PW (0.24–0.26); PPL (0.32–0.36); PPW (0.33–0.36); GL (1.04–1.08); TL (4.77–5.21); CI (88.46–93.61); SI (70.83–78.26); OI (22.72– 24.44). Midsized. Shiny integument. Brownish body, yellowish leg (except for coxa) and antenna. Thin and branched setae, midsized to short, suberect to subdecumbent, 2 short branches of equal size diverging from the main axis (
Fig. 80D
).
